	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f104162565668845><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=15971&mid=104162565668845>Long Spawn on Kerzar</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=15971&mid=104162565668845#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145256><span id= >Finn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>8 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jan 3rd 3:54 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just a little tip for those of you doing this quest.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm currently working on this on the Rathe, and got a group together to take down Kerzar Clawtore.  I handed the orders in to Legionnaire Fallion, and proceeded to have the 2 druids with me track the zone for Kerzar.  We did this for about 15-20 minutes, and he didn't pop.  I was convinced the quest was yet another broken one.  One of the druids left, and the rest of us went to the vamp castle to do some hunting, and, probably about 30-45 minutes AFTER I handed in the orders to Legionnairre Fallion, who comes strolling up and stops right outside the castle but Kerzar!  I can't express how happy I was after thinking the quest was broken.  Anyway, a 52 Pally (me), a 53 Druid and 2 low 50's necros had no problems at all with him.  Don't try fear kiting as the snare didn't seem to stick and he runs FAST.  Since the necros couldn't get into Katta (KoS), I had to wait to do the next battle - I'll try to keep you all updated as it goes.  The 4 coterie generals were a pain (Our druid was down to 181 HP after they swarmed him), but we all had SoE on and just got out of their agro range.<br>&nbsp;<br>Maccullen Boru<br>52 Paladin - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105699" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105699</a><br>Mirth and Mayhem<br><a href="http://www.mirthandmayhem.com" target=_new>http://www.mirthandmayhem.com</a><br>The Rathe<br></td></tr>
