	   <tr><td colspan=2>/sigh.&nbsp;&nbsp;The pottery was easy - I spent a couple of hours getting it up to 50, but I don't think I even needed to do that.  If you have a zero, just take the sketch, clay and water and keep trying till you get it.  The firing was trivial even at 50 pottery, so I suspect that's a no fail act.  The shade lord battle was pretty easy too.  It takes place in the very middle of that Mage building.  If you keep your group in the middle of that area, you won't get the 3 shades who pop to even add.  Unfortunately, it was after this that I screwed up.  I had read on Paladins of Norrath that the Vampire Volatilis Ashes were tradeable, and sure enough - they were for sale in the bazaar.  So, after getting the medallion from the mages, I took everything back to Phenic to turn in.  He ate the 2 symbols I had spent all week working on, but returned the ashes. :(  Apparently, Heriatus drops ashes of the same name, and I didn't think to identify.  Oh well - back to square one.  In any case, hopefully this will help anyone else who might try to take the easy way out - if you see the ashes in the bazaar, ask to identify before you buy them.<br>&nbsp;<br>Maccullen Boru<br>52 Paladin - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105699" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105699</a><br>Mirth and Mayhem<br><a href="http://www.mirthandmayhem.com" target=_new>http://www.mirthandmayhem.com</a><br>The Rathe<br></td></tr>
